This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the challenges of adapting unsupervised approaches to speech processing, which is a subfield of natural language processing. The paper also discusses the unsupervised induction of semantic representations of words and sentences, which is a common topic in the cs.CL sub-category. 

The paper may also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with speech processing and the analysis of spoken language. 

Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it discusses unsupervised learning models for speech processing. 

Finally, the paper may be relevant to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it discusses the challenges of transferring methods from synthetic speech to natural speech, which may involve analyzing social and information networks of spoken language.
